I"M<p>176 homes on the Treverton estate have been earmarked for redevelopment in <a href="https://planningconsult.rbkc.gov.uk/gf2.ti/f/782882/24784549.1/PDF/-/Considerations_for_Estate_Regeneration_Proposals__Treverton_Estate_January_2017.pdf">this Jan 2017 Cabinet report</a>.</p>

<p>Six months later the plans for all three of the borough’s estate regeneration schemes were <a href="https://www.insidehousing.co.uk/news/news/kensington-and-chelsea-council-pauses-schemes-51587">paused</a> after the Grenfell disaster happened.</p>

<p>The borough’s <a href="https://www.rbkc.gov.uk/sites/default/files/atoms/files/2019%20LOCAL%20PLAN%20SECTION%201%20SPATIAL%20STRATEGY.pdf">Local Plan says</a> that the schemes will only now be progressed with the consent of estate residents via a ballot:</p>

